# 📝 User Feedback Dashboard

A full-stack web application that allows users to submit feedback via a form and lets administrators view, sort, and filter all submissions in a clean dashboard. Built using **React**, **Tailwind CSS**, **Node.js**, **Express**, and **MongoDB**.

---

## 🚀 Features

- Submit feedback with username, email, category, title, and detailed text.
- Dashboard to **filter by category**, **sort by fields**, and **search easily**.
- Responsive, aesthetic UI built with **Tailwind CSS**.
- API connected via **Express and MongoDB** (Mongoose).

---

## 🛠️ Tech Stack

- **Frontend**: React + Tailwind CSS
- **Backend**: Node.js + Express
- **Database**: MongoDB (via Mongoose)
- **Axios** for HTTP requests
- **React Router DOM** for routing

---

📦 Clone & Run Locally

1. **Clone the repository**

git clone https://github.com/YOUR_USERNAME/YOUR_REPO_NAME.git
cd YOUR_REPO_NAME

2. Set up the backend

    cd backend
    npm install

✨ Create a .env file
Inside the /backend folder, create a .env file with:

    DB_URI=mongodb+srv://<your-mongo-connection-string>
    PORT=3000

Start the backend:
    
    npm start

3. Set up the frontend

    cd ../frontend
npm install
npm run dev

Open your browser and go to:
📍 http://localhost:5173

